5 // A Status encapsulates the result of an operation. It may indicate success,
6 // or it may indicate an error with an associated error message.
7 //
8 // Multiple threads can invoke const methods on a Status without
9 // external synchronization, but if any of the threads may call a
10 // non-const method, all threads accessing the same Status must use
11 // external synchronization.
12 
13 // Adapted from Apache Kudu, TensorFlow

32 #define ARROW_RETURN_NOT_OK(s) \
33  do { \
34  ::arrow::Status _s = (s); \
35  if (ARROW_PREDICT_FALSE(!_s.ok())) { \
36  std::stringstream ss; \
37  ss << __FILE__ << ":" << __LINE__ << " code: " << #s << "\n" << _s.message(); \
38  return Status(_s.code(), ss.str()); \
39  } \
40  } while (0)
41 
42 #else
43 
44 #define ARROW_RETURN_NOT_OK(s) \
45  do { \
46  ::arrow::Status _s = (s); \
47  if (ARROW_PREDICT_FALSE(!_s.ok())) { \
48  return _s; \
49  } \
50  } while (false)
51 
52 #endif // ARROW_EXTRA_ERROR_CONTEXT
53 
54 #define RETURN_NOT_OK_ELSE(s, else_) \
55  do { \
56  ::arrow::Status _s = (s); \
57  if (!_s.ok()) { \
58  else_; \
59  return _s; \
60  } \
61  } while (false)

95 class ARROW_EXPORT Status {
96  public:
97  // Create a success status.
98  Status() noexcept : state_(NULL) {}
99  ~Status() noexcept {
100  // ARROW-2400: On certain compilers, splitting off the slow path improves
101  // performance significantly.
102  if (ARROW_PREDICT_FALSE(state_ != NULL)) {
103  DeleteState();
104  }
105  }
106

186  // Returns true iff the status indicates success.
187  bool ok() const { return (state_ == NULL); }
188 
189  bool IsOutOfMemory() const { return code() == StatusCode::OutOfMemory; }
190  bool IsKeyError() const { return code() == StatusCode::KeyError; }
191  bool IsInvalid() const { return code() == StatusCode::Invalid; }
192  bool IsIOError() const { return code() == StatusCode::IOError; }
193  bool IsCapacityError() const { return code() == StatusCode::CapacityError; }
194  bool IsTypeError() const { return code() == StatusCode::TypeError; }
195  bool IsUnknownError() const { return code() == StatusCode::UnknownError; }
196  bool IsNotImplemented() const { return code() == StatusCode::NotImplemented; }
197  // An object could not be serialized or deserialized.
198  bool IsSerializationError() const { return code() == StatusCode::SerializationError; }
199  // An error from R
200  bool IsRError() const { return code() == StatusCode::RError; }
201  // An error is propagated from a nested Python function.
202  bool IsPythonError() const { return code() == StatusCode::PythonError; }
203  // An object with this object ID already exists in the plasma store.
204  bool IsPlasmaObjectExists() const { return code() == StatusCode::PlasmaObjectExists; }
205  // An object was requested that doesn't exist in the plasma store.
206  bool IsPlasmaObjectNonexistent() const {
207  return code() == StatusCode::PlasmaObjectNonexistent;
208  }
209  // An already sealed object is tried to be sealed again.
210  bool IsPlasmaObjectAlreadySealed() const {
211  return code() == StatusCode::PlasmaObjectAlreadySealed;
212  }
213  // An object is too large to fit into the plasma store.
214  bool IsPlasmaStoreFull() const { return code() == StatusCode::PlasmaStoreFull; }
215 
216  bool IsStillExecuting() const { return code() == StatusCode::StillExecuting; }
217 
218  // Return a string representation of this status suitable for printing.
219  // Returns the string "OK" for success.
220  std::string ToString() const;
221 
222  // Return a string representation of the status code, without the message
223  // text or posix code information.
224  std::string CodeAsString() const;
225 
226  StatusCode code() const { return ok() ? StatusCode::OK : state_->code; }
227 
228  std::string message() const { return ok() ? "" : state_->msg; }

230  private:
231  struct State {
232  StatusCode code;
233  std::string msg;
234  };
235  // OK status has a `NULL` state_. Otherwise, `state_` points to
236  // a `State` structure containing the error code and message(s)
237  State* state_;
238 
239  void DeleteState() {
240  delete state_;
241  state_ = NULL;
242  }
243  void CopyFrom(const Status& s);
244  void MoveFrom(Status& s);
245 };

252 inline void Status::MoveFrom(Status& s) {
253  delete state_;
254  state_ = s.state_;
255  s.state_ = NULL;
256 }
257 
258 inline Status::Status(const Status& s)
259  : state_((s.state_ == NULL) ? NULL : new State(*s.state_)) {}
260 
261 inline Status& Status::operator=(const Status& s) {
262  // The following condition catches both aliasing (when this == &s),
263  // and the common case where both s and *this are ok.
264  if (state_ != s.state_) {
265  CopyFrom(s);
266  }
267  return *this;
268 }
269 
270 inline Status::Status(Status&& s) noexcept : state_(s.state_) { s.state_ = NULL; }
271 
272 inline Status& Status::operator=(Status&& s) noexcept {
273  MoveFrom(s);
274  return *this;
275 }
276 
277 inline Status Status::operator&(const Status& s) const noexcept {
278  if (ok()) {
279  return s;
280  } else {
281  return *this;
282  }
283 }
284 
285 inline Status Status::operator&(Status&& s) const noexcept {
286  if (ok()) {
287  return std::move(s);
288  } else {
289  return *this;
290  }
291 }
292 
293 inline Status& Status::operator&=(const Status& s) noexcept {
294  if (ok() && !s.ok()) {
295  CopyFrom(s);
296  }
297  return *this;
298 }
299 
300 inline Status& Status::operator&=(Status&& s) noexcept {
301  if (ok() && !s.ok()) {
302  MoveFrom(s);
303  }
304  return *this;
